{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀνοχή</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>holding back, stopping,</b> especially of hostilities: hence mostly in <i>plural</i>, <b>armistice, truce,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.4.17\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀνοχὰς ποιεῖσθαι Canon Laws texts cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.164; διδόναι 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 8.68; σπείσασθαι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pelopidas” 29; αἱ Καλλισθένους ἀ. 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.31; αἱ ἑξαετεῖς ἀ. 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 3.59\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; compare ἀνοκωχή. <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>time, opportunity,</b> οὐκ ἔδωκεν αὐτοῖς ἀνοχὴν ἐμβατεῦσαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.12.25\">LXX</a>]; ἡμερῶν ἀ. <b>delay</b> of some days, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1068.15 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>plural</i>, ἀνοχαί, = Latin <i>feriae,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 39.30. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> ἀνοχαὶδικῶν, = Latin <i>iustitium,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 55.26. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (ἀνέχομαι) <b>long-suffering, forbearance,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"NT.Rom.2.4, 3.26. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> ἀνοχὴν ἀναπαύλης διδόναι <b>permission</b> to rest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 3.6.10. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>relief from</b> disease, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Philumenus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus “Synopsis” 8.3.4. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ={ἀνατολή}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 4.157, 5